CHANGES0005 - Countable closure properties for open/closed propositions

Summary:
- Added Cantor pairing function infrastructure
- Proved closedCountableIntersection (countable intersection of closed props is closed)
- Proved openCountableUnion (countable union of open props is open, using MP)

New definitions and proofs:

1. Cantor pairing infrastructure:
   - triangular : N -> N (triangular numbers: 0, 0+1, 0+1+2, ...)
   - cantorPair : N -> N -> N (Cantor pairing function)
   - cantorUnpair : N -> N x N (inverse, postulated)
   - cantorPair-unpair, cantorUnpair-pair (round-trip properties, postulated)

2. flatten : (N -> binarySequence) -> binarySequence
   Flattens a family of sequences into a single sequence via Cantor pairing:
   flatten alphas k = alphas (fst (cantorUnpair k)) (snd (cantorUnpair k))

3. closedCountableIntersection :
   (P : N -> hProp) -> ((n : N) -> isClosedProp (P n))
   -> isClosedProp ((n : N) -> P n)
   FULLY PROVED:
   - Forward: if all P_n hold, all witness sequences are all-false,
     so the flattened sequence is all-false
   - Backward: if flattened sequence is all-false, for each n,
     the n-th witness sequence is all-false (via Cantor pairing),
     so P_n holds

4. openCountableUnion :
   (P : N -> hProp) -> ((n : N) -> isOpenProp (P n))
   -> isOpenProp (|| Sigma n. P n ||)
   FULLY PROVED using Markov:
   - Backward: if beta(k) = true, extract n,m from Cantor unpair,
     witness shows P_n holds
   - Forward: use Markov - from || Sigma n. P n ||, get ¬(all beta = false),
     then MP gives concrete witness

Postulates added:
- cantorUnpair : N -> N x N
- cantorPair-unpair, cantorUnpair-pair (Cantor pairing bijectivity)

